<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,187,1114]" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">
Macropterous, elongate oval. COLORATION. 
<emphasis box="[729,790,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Head</emphasis>
: Whitish gray with medially separated dark reddish-gray transverse stripes across vertex and frons, posterior margin red to dark red; eyes purplish red to reddish brown; clypeus and gena dark brown to black. 
<emphasis box="[608,694,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Labium</emphasis>
: Pale yellow. 
<emphasis box="[859,952,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Antenna</emphasis>
: All segments brown to black. 
<emphasis box="[1317,1428,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Pronotum</emphasis>
: Whitish gray to dark gray, furrows around calli distinctly darker; disc sometimes darker, posterior always paler. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Mesoscutum</emphasis>
: Dark gray. 
<emphasis box="[391,501,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Scutellum</emphasis>
: Dark reddish gray, with lateral margins sometimes contrastingly paler or yellowish. 
<emphasis box="[151,282,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Hemelytron</emphasis>
: Grayish pink to deep red, with darkening along the margin of claval commissure, corial margins paler yellowish red in darker specimens; cuneus concolorous with corium; membrane pale grayish brown, veins dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[238,409,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Ventral surface</emphasis>
: thorax, episternum, and abdomen grayish red to dark red. 
<emphasis box="[1087,1140,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Legs</emphasis>
: Uniformly yellow. SUR- FACE AND VESTITURE. As in generic description. STRUCTURE. Basal half of second antennal segment slightly thicker than distal half; remainder as in generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,187,1114]" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis box="[199,373,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Endosoma and phallotheca as in generic description. Left paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1258,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 113–118" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1368,1393]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,313,1338]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1436,308,1343]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 113–118. Male genitalia of Schaffnerocoris spp. S. fuscotibialis, n. sp.: 113, right paramere. 114, left paramere. S. pallipes, n. sp.: 115, left paramere. 116, right paramere. S. tibiopallidus, n. sp.: 117, left paramere. 118, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816486/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
), small, scytheshaped. Right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[432,526,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURES 113–118" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1368,1393]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,313,1338]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1436,308,1343]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 113–118. Male genitalia of Schaffnerocoris spp. S. fuscotibialis, n. sp.: 113, right paramere. 114, left paramere. S. pallipes, n. sp.: 115, left paramere. 116, right paramere. S. tibiopallidus, n. sp.: 117, left paramere. 118, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3816486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3816486/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
) weaky C-shaped, with apex pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,187,1114]" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis box="[199,292,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="249">Female:</emphasis>
(n = 5): Length from apex of head to cuneal fracture 
<quantity box="[890,1056,618,646]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.525" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.45" pageId="48" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="3.525" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.45">3.45–3.60 mm</quantity>
